  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">UNES:Advocacy and climate change.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Articulation of a dialogue table for the definition of priorities in the use of water and soil in San Francisco Men&#xE9;ndez and San Juli&#xE1;n.
2. Strengthened the network of climate monitors in 7 communities of San Francisco Men&#xE9;ndez and created a network of climate monitors in communities of San Juli&#xE1;n.
3. Advocacy actions about climate change issues at national and international level.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. OSC of San Francisco Menendez and San Juli&#xE1;n has achieved at the inter-institutional dialogue table agreements for the benefit of communities in the use of water and soil
2. Strengthened early alert systems and climate change adaptation practices in rural communities of San Francisco Menendez and San Julian.
3. Promoted political and normative changes at national/regional levels in climate change for the benefit of the poor and marginalized population.</narrative>
  </description>
